rning-as-philippine-activists-sail-towards-disputed-reef%2Farticleshow%2F110164258.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fchina-sees-red-issues-warning-as-philippine-activists-sail-towards-disputed-reef%2Famp_articleshow%2F110164258.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fchina-sees-red-issues-warning-as-philippine-activists-sail-towards-disputed-reef%2Famp_articleshow%2F110164258.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22170%20Bison%20Herd%20Could%20Offset%20CO2%20Equal%20To%202%20Million%20Cars%2C%20Study%20Finds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EResearchers%20studying%20European%20bison%20in%20Romania%20have%20found%20that%20these%20large%20herbivores%20may%20be%20a%20powerful%20tool%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20climate%20change.%20A%20herd%20of%20just%20170%20bison%20could%20store%20an%20amount%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20(CO2)%20equivalent%20to%20taking%20nearly%202%20million%20cars%20off%20the%20road%20for%20a%20year%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20model%20developed%20by%20scientists%20at%20the%20Yale%20School%20of%20the%20Environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20which%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20peer-reviewed%2C%20highlights%20the%20importance%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20maintaining%20healthy%20ecosystems.%20The%20model%20calculates%20the%20additional%20CO2%20that%20animals%20like%20bison%20help%20capture%20and%20store%20in%20the%20soil%20through%20their%20natural%20behaviours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBison%20influences%20grassland%20and%20forest%20ecosystems%20by%20grazing%20grasslands%20evenly%2C%20recycling%20nutrients%20to%20fertilise%20the%20soil%20and%20all%20of%20its%20life%2C%20dispersing%20seeds%20to%20enrich%20the%20ecosystem%2C%20and%20compacting%20the%20soil%20to%20prevent%20stored%20carbon%20from%20being%20released%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20lead%20author%20Prof.%20Oswald%20Schmitz%20of%20Yale%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2Farticle%2F2024%2Fmay%2F15%2Fbison-romania-tarcu-2m-cars-carbon-dioxide-emissions-aoe%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20creatures%20evolved%20for%20millions%20of%20years%20with%20grassland%20and%20forest%20ecosystems%2C%20and%20their%20removal%2C%20especially%20where%20grasslands%20have%20been%20ploughed%20up%2C%20has%20led%20to%20the%20release%20of%20vast%20amounts%20of%20carbon.%20Restoring%20these%20ecosystems%20can%20bring%20back%20balance%2C%20and%20'rewilded'%20bison%20are%20some%20of%20the%20climate%20heroes%20that%20can%20help%20achieve%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Lees%2C%20a%20reader%20in%20biodiversity%20at%20Manchester%20Metropolitan%20University%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20with%20the%20study%2C%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bmakes%20a%20convincing%20case%20for%20European%20bison%20reintroduction%20as%20a%20nature-based%20climate%20solution-one%20with%20major%20biodiversity%20conservation%20co-benefits.%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20team%20studied%20a%20herd%20of%20European%20bison%20reintroduced%20to%20Romania's%20Arcu%20Mountains%20in%202014.%20The%20species%20had%20been%20absent%20from%20the%20region%20for%20nearly%20200%20years%2C%20but%20today%20the%20Arcu%20Mountains%20boast%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20free-roaming%20bison%20populations%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715831280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Ffvs5o928_bison_625x300_16_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2F170-bison-herd-could-offset-co2-equal-to-2-million-cars-study-finds-5674007%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Researchers%20studying%20European%20bison%20in%20Romania%20find%20that%20a%20herd%20of%20170%20bison%20could%20store%20an%20amount%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20equivalent%20to%20taking%20nearly%202%20million%