vice%20currently%20operating%20in%20multiple%20US%20cities%2C%20with%20plans%20to%20launch%20in%20more.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWaymo%20is%20Alphabet's%20robotaxi%20service%20formerly%20known%20as%20the%20Google%20Self-Driving%20Car%20Project.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWaymo's%20driverless%20taxis%20are%20currently%20operating%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELike%20its%20main%20competitor%2C%20Cruise%2C%20Waymo's%20autonomous%20vehicles%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20accidents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWaymo%20is%20a%20robotaxi%20service%20owned%20by%20Google's%20parent%20company%2C%20Alphabet%20Inc.%20It%20was%20initially%20formed%20by%20Google%20and%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-car-project-history-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Self-Driving%20Car%20Project%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20following%20seven%20years%20of%20research%20and%20development%20before%20eventually%20being%20spun%20out%20to%20its%20own%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20started%20developing%20Waymo%20and%20its%20self-driving%20technology%20in%202009%20at%20the%20Google%20X%20lab%2C%20which%20was%20led%20by%20Google%20co-founder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsergey-brin-career-life-education%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESergey%20Brin%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20almost%20two%20years%20of%20testing%20the%20technology%2C%20Google%20and%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20revealed%20its%20existence%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20lawmakers%20raised%20concerns%20at%20the%20time%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20regulations%20for%20this%20new%20technological%20front.%20Google%20was%20a%20prominent%20supporter%2C%20lobbying%20for%20regulation.%20By%202012%2C%20Nevada's%20Department%20of%20Motor%20Vehicles%20had%20licensed%20a%20self-driving%20Prius%20running%20Google's%20software.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20time%