f%20getting%20an%20aerospace%20job%20in%20the%20US%20without%20a%20citizenship%20or%20a%20green%20card.%20To%20be%20accepted%20as%20a%20doctoral%20candidate%20at%20MIT%2C%20she%20would%20need%20some%20work%20experience%2C%20she%20learned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20came%20here%20alone%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20support.%20I%20kept%20doing%20research%20projects%20and%20publishing%20papers%20to%20add%20to%20my%20credentials%20to%20show%20that%20I%20can%20create%20an%20impact.%20Every%20opportunity%20I%20got%20was%20never%20luck%20or%20coincidence%2C%20it%20was%20through%20hard%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20engineer%20shares.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20pursuing%20her%20masters%2C%20she%20started%20writing%20to%20professors%20at%20MIT%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20them%20for%20her%20PhD.%20It%20was%20only%20on%20her%20third%20attempt%20that%20she%20was%20selected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20honed%20my%20skills%20and%20worked%20outside%20my%20curriculum%20but%20was%20still%20waitlisted%20as%20not%20all%20space%20projects%20can%20take%20foreign%20nationals%20since%20they%20are%20funded%20by%20the%20US%20government%20and%20have%20restrictions.%20But%20when%20I%20was%20waitlisted%20the%20second%20time%2C%20I%20wrote%20to%20all%20the%20professors%20at%20MIT%20asking%20for%20a%20chance%20to%20work%20with%20them%20for%20a%20year.%20Finally%2C%20I%20heard%20back%20from%20professor%20Sara%20Seager%20that%20there%20was%20a%20project%20I%20could%20work%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Seager%20is%20an%20astrophysicist%20and%20planetary%20scientist%20at%20MIT%20who%20focuses%20on%20exoplanet%20research%2C%20which%20is%20the%20discovery%20of%20new%20planets.%20She%20offered%20her%20a%20temporary%20research%20associate%20position%20for%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20time%2C%20Akshata%20had%20two%20options%20%E2%80%94%20take%20a%20well-paying%20job%20at%20the%20likes%20of%20Google%20or%20Ama