9CMy%20doctorate%20is%20in%20aeronautics%20and%20astronautics%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebut%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20boundary%20of%20science%20and%20engineering%2C%20focusing%20on%20developing%20space%20telescopes%20and%20technologies%20to%20discover%20new%20planets%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20went%20on%20to%20work%20full-time%20at%20the%20NASA%20JPL%2C%20which%2C%20she%20shares%2C%20was%20also%20a%20serendipitous%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20worked%20there%20for%20three%20months%20as%20an%20intern%20and%20would%20meet%20with%20managers%20everyday%20asking%20for%20a%20job.%20But%20nobody%20could%20commit%20anything%20to%20me%20without%20a%20green%20card%20as%20it%20involves%20a%20lot%20of%20paperwork%20and%20complexity%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20day%20of%20her%20internship%20arrived%20but%20she%20still%20had%20no%20job%20offers%20or%20interviews.%20Luckily%2C%20she%20had%20a%20presentation%20to%20give%20that%20day.%20A%20hiring%20manager%20in%20the%20audience%20was%20impressed%20with%20Akshata%E2%80%99s%20presentation%20and%20decided%20to%20give%20her%20a%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20then%2C%20till%20the%20paperwork%20came%20through%2C%20the%20scientist%20recalls%20that%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20breathe%20easy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20entered%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F323066%2Fchandrayaan-3-the-history-of-how-india-began-one-of-its-most-significant-space-journeys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20JPL%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20employee%20in%20February%202020%2C%20that%20was%20one%20of%20the%20happiest%20days%20of%20her%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Akshata%E2%80%99s%20story%20is%20surely%20inspirational%2C%20we%20ask%2C%20what%20kept%20her%20going%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20adamant%20about%20getting%20into%20NASA%20and%20doing%20whatever%20it%20